# @THSHV01P116A_BEG_WMSAH
VAR_HKMXV03P050C VAR_HKMXV04P038B ووجدنا محمد بن علي بن داود قد حدثنا قال حدثنا حاجب بن الوليد حدثنا محمد بن سلمة عن ابن إسحاق عن سعيد بن أبي سعيد المقبري عن أبيه عن عقبة بن عامر قال كنت أسير مع رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم بين الجحفة والأبواء إذ غشينا ريح وظلمة فجعل رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم يتعوذ ب @QURS113A001_BEG قل أعوذ برب الفلق @QURS113A001_END و @QURS114A001_BEG قل أعوذ برب الناس @QURS114A001_END ويقول يا عقبة تعوذ فما تعوذ متعوذ بمثلهما ثم سمعته يؤمنا بهما في الصلاة @THSHV01P116A_END_WMSAH
PageV01P116
# @COMMENT: Passage not found in HSNX. According to WSACD and WMHNS, the passage refers a version of the Qurʾān copied by Ubayy b. Kaʿb that contained two Qurʾānic passages, Q113:001 and Q114:001. Ubayy b. Kaʿb is mentioned twice by WZATB in HSNX: as a participant at Badr (HSNXV01P703C) and as receiving two shares from the dispribution of lots following Khaybar (HSNXV02P358A). Ibn Isḥāq quotes traditions from Ubayy b. Kaʿb extensively in WSFAB on different sections of the Qurʾān, as does WSACD. According to Muḥammad b. Saʿd, Ubayy was was among the first people of Yabrib to give allegiance to Muḥammad at ʿAqabah and was unusual in that he was literate. He made copies of sections of the Qurʾān in Muḥammad’s lifetime and was one of the most important memorizers of the text. He was one of the people ʿUthmān turned to in producing the so-called ʿUthmānī Codex. @EC_01/17/23@

