# @COMMENT: This passage is not in HSNX. Khuwaylah bint Ḥakīm is only mentioned once in the witness of WZATB (see HSNXV02P484C) in the story of the capture of Ṭāʾif where she asks Muḥammad for the jewelry of specific women among the Thaqīf (also see WSFAB in TBRCV03P085A). The HBHXV43P334A passage above must take place before the events described in HSNXV02P484C because occurs after the death of ʿUthmān b. Maẓʿūn. According to al-Ṭabarī (TBRCV02P458), ʿUthmān b. Maẓʿūn died in Dhū al-Ḥijjah in the year 2 after or during the Battle of Sawīq, that occurred at that time. 
