PageV02P779
# @COMMENT: Abū Bakrah, or his ism Masrūḥ, are not mentioned in HSNX. He was Nufayʿ b. al-Ḥārith b. Kaladah b. ʿAmr al-Thaqafī. Some say his name was Masrūḥ. He was one of four slaves who came out from Ṭāʾif whom the prophet freed. He was a companion and a source of some traditions. He died in the year 52/672 (HJTTV10P469A-470A). Abū Bakrah is mentioned in WSFAB is a passage treating the same topic but constructed completely differently. He is also mentioned in WYBWS and WJHZA also in reference to Ṭāʾif. The name clairification is also found in WYBWS, WMUAL, and WSACD.

